TWO WORDS
written by Zachary Theilen
proof of concept based on an idea discussed with Phil Juarez

Running the app using this method requires the host computer to have Python 3 installed, 3.10 preferred.

1. Clone git repository to your local machine
    * open a terminal and navigate to your desired location
    * type the following and press enter:
        git clone https://github.com/computernerdzach/two-words.git

2. Run locally
    * navigate to the newly downloaded directory and enter the project
        cd two-words
    * launch the application:
        python3 gui.py

